The paper deals with the problem of estimating the relative rigid pose between two RGB-D scans of the same environment, which is a fundamental problem in computer vision, robotics, and computer graphics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel deep neural network for this task, which involves scene completion and matching on completed scans, indicating a possible connection to the sub-category cs.GR (Graphics). The use of deep neural networks suggests a possible connection to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The problem of relative pose estimation is also relevant to robotics, which suggests a possible connection to the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on benchmark datasets, indicating a possible connection to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
